@node Installation

Make sure that @{"amarquee.library" link amarquee.library} v44+ is installed
in your LIBS: directory!

To install QSendFile, run the included Installer script
and follow its directions.  Or, if you prefer to do it by hand:

Put the line:

QSendFile     2958/tcp

in your AmiTCP:db/services file.

Also, put the line

QSendFile   stream     tcp nowait root   c:QSendFile

in your AmiTCP:db/inet.conf file.  Note that if you are keeping the QSendFile
executable somewhere besides c:, you will need to modify the last field of
this line to reflect its true position.

And then re-start AmiTCP to make sure the changes take effect.

Also:

To run QSendFile from QAmiTrack, put the following line into
the ToolTypes of the QAmiTrack icon:

ACTION7=Send File,c:QSendFile %h

(Of course, any free ACTION ToolType may be used, not just 7 ;))
@endnode


@node Using
 
Using QSendFile is fairly simple.  To send a file, type:

QSendFile computer.name.com filename

(substituting the correct IP name for computer.name.com, and the
correct file name for file name, of course).  If you do not specify
a file name, an ASL requester will open to allow you to specify a
file.

The receiving Amiga (which must also have QSendFile installed)
will open up a requester asking his permission to download the
file.  The receiving user will have the option of downloading
your file to the same directory (on his computer) that the file
is on on your computer, or to choose a different directory.

Either user may abort at any time by clicking the close box in
their transmission window.

@endnode

